      "body" : "Link says that &quot;[...] an allocation failure occurs [...] and a stop-the-world (STW) full collection is done.&quot;, therefore &quot;allocation failure&quot; is a <b>cause</b> and GC is <b>recovery action</b> (outcome if you prefer). What kind of GC it would be if outcome is &quot;allocation failure&quot;? Both &quot;GC&quot; and &quot;Full GC&quot; are recovery actions. &quot;Full GC&quot; is just slower and more expensive therefore if it happens often there may be a problem."
